EmailTemplate.description: Request BM for IRIS implementation in ZM
EmailTemplate.name: ZM exercice
EmailTemplate.subject: Ref nr {!Case.CaseNumber} - {!Case.Subject}
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear Sir/Madam,
In order to enable the use of USD currency for the remittance & settlement operations in Zambia, IATA is currently implementing and enhancing its financial systems. For that reason, and taking into consideration the security involved in the setup of bank accounts, IATA is requiring your airline to submit a Local Bank Account Mandate related to an USD currency bank account opened in Zambia.
In order to complete this process, we would like to request the issuance of a bank mandate containing the information as per attached template and guidelines. The bank mandate must be issued from your Company’s Head Office and signed by two Head Office senior officers, at least one of which must be:
• Chief Financial Officer (CFO) or
• Head of Treasury or Cash Management Department
The original document should be sent to IATA Geneva on the following address:
Airline Participation
International Air Transport Association
33, Route de l'Aéroport
1215 Geneva
Switzerland
Ref nr {!Case.CaseNumber}
We would be grateful if you could provide us with the original mandate to the address above mentioned at the care of the undersigned, by June, 20th.
Thank you in advance for your cooperation and should you need any further assistance, please do not hesitate to contact us.
Best Regards
{!Case.OwnerFullName}
Global Airline Participation Team
Financial and Distribution Services
International Air Transport Association
33, Route de l'Aéroport
1215 Geneva 15 Airport
Switzerland
www.iata.org/customer
